Dado,
You might also consider flying out of Concord (CCR), which is about 35
miles north east of SF. I liked it because the airport itself is very
challenging and fun to taxi around with its 2 sets of intersecting
runways. Another benefit is that even on windy days, you can always
find a favorable runway with not much crosswind and you can usually
learn to tackle strong crosswinds by requesting other runways.
I personally know many good instructors in CCR and will be happy to
pass along the info if you need it. Good luck,

-Girish

